   <body>
      <p>The Adobe Sign Services API is installed with the Adobe Sign managed package and can be exposed to external applications via a Salesforce site or community. </p>
      <p>
         <table>
            <tgroup cols="1">
               <colspec colname="col1"/>
               <tbody>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>
                           <codeph>https://{<xref href="http://testmanaged--clmauto3.my.salesforce.com"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external">
                                 <u>testmanaged--clmauto3.my.salesforce.com</u>
                              </xref>}/services/apexrest/Apttus_Echosign/echosignIntegration/v1</codeph>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                           <codeph>/agreements/:agreementId/sendForESignature</codeph>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </p>
      <p>You must replace this path <codeph>{<xref href="http://testmanaged--clmauto3.my.salesforce.com"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external">
               <u>testmanaged--clmauto3.my.salesforce.com</u>
            </xref>}</codeph> with your Salesforce org path.</p>
